A new species of the leafhopper genus
Satsumanus Ishihara, 1953
from India (Hempiptera: Cicadellidae : Deltocephalinae )

Leafhoppers, family 
Cicadellidae
, are one of the largest and economically important insect families, with approximately 22,000 described species (

; 

). Among 
Cicadellidae
, subfamily 
Deltocephalinae
is the most diverse, largest and economically important, comprising 38 tribes, 923 genera and at least 7000 valid species (

; 

). The tribe 
Opsiini
is distinguished from other tribes as follows: face oblique, not strongly depressed, not concave in profile; anterior margin of head without carinae; antennal bases near middle or posteroventral (lower) corner of eyes; gena not extended onto dorsum behind eyes; stem of connective long and bifurcated; aedeagus with two gonopores (

; 

). This tribe is economically important as vectors of viral, bacterial, phytoplasma, and spiroplasma phytopathogens (

; 

; 

; 

). 

revised the classification of 
Deltocephalinae
based on molecular and morphological data and provided a revised interpretation of 
Opsiini
with four subtribes Achaeticina, Circuliferina, Eremophlepsiina, and 
Opsiina
. These subtribes comprise 41 genera (

; 

